Looking for Software Developers
text:
Brief intro: I am an ex-scientist who moved to scientific sales. I started developing a tool for myself which turned into an exciting SaaS product - solid value proposition, keen interest from my network, positive feedback on an early prototype.

Our tech stack is the following: - AWS cloud and EC2 instances for hosting FE and BE - MongoDB for the storage database - Go Lang is on the backend serving the rest API endpoints (might move to nodejs/nestjs) - FE is done as monolith React SPA

The company is set up and interest is growing, but both of my developers are working part-time, so we are looking for extra hands to join us in developing MVP.

At the moment we all work pro bono, but shed no tears - we can offer referrals, recommendations, paid positions in the future, and of course, an exciting project to work on.

Don't get stuck in one project as Bill Gates did - get in touch to see how you could join!

Show HN: Projectbook – a free collection of 100 project ideas for learning
text:
I've been hoarding ideas for what would make good learning projects when exploring new languages, frameworks, and libraries for years. So I decided to flesh those ideas out, create some mock-ups, and share them with the public. I originally just had ~20 projects, but as I kept working on it, more ideas kept coming up and it ended up coming to 109 ideas so far. Hope they offer some inspiration or guidance for those trying to learn but not sure what to build.

Projectbook is free and open source. Contributions are welcome. And I'll keep adding to it as I come across ideas, resources, and implementations.
